South Africa has recorded 3 751 new coronavirus infections in the last 24-hour cycle, taking the total number to 1 466 767. The country has also recorded 261 new COVID-19 related fatalities on Thursday. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in KwaZulu-Natal. “Regrettably, we report 261 more COVID-19 related deaths: 44 from Eastern Cape, 12 from the Free State, 53 from Gauteng, 56 from KwaZulu-Natal, 11 from Limpopo, 42 from the North West, 2 from the Northern Cape and 41 from the Western Cape,” says Dr Mkhize.  This brings the total number of deaths to 45 605. Recoveries currently stand at 1 327 186. The cumulative number of tests conducted to date is 8 400 319. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 1 466 767, the total number of deaths is 45 605 and the total number of recoveries is 1 327 186. pic.twitter.com/2aI9MQAD3d — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) February 4, 2021 